## Non-Negotiable Rules

### TypeScript
- Strict mode is on. No `any`. No `as any`.
- All function parameters and return types must be explicitly typed.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for object shapes.
- Use discriminated unions over optional chaining where possible.

### Data Fetching
- Server Components → fetch directly with `db.*` (Prisma)
- Client Components → TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`)
- Forms → Server Actions + `useActionState` + Zod
- Never use `useEffect` + `useState` to fetch server data
- Never use API routes for internal data reads — only for webhooks and external integrations

### Server Actions pattern (always follow exactly)
```typescript
"use server"

import { auth } from "@/lib/auth"
import { db } from "@/lib/db"
import { z } from "zod"
import { redirect } from "next/navigation"

const Schema = z.object({ ... })
export type ActionState = { errors?: ...; message?: string }

export async function myAction(prev: ActionState, formData: FormData): Promise<ActionState> {
  const session = await auth()
  if (!session?.user?.id) return { message: "Unauthorised" }

  const parsed = Schema.safeParse(Object.fromEntries(formData))
  if (!parsed.success) return { errors: parsed.error.flatten().fieldErrors }

  await db.model.create({ data: parsed.data })
  redirect("/destination")
}
```

### Components
- Props-only — components never fetch their own data
- `"use client"` must be the literal first line for client components
- Co-locate Server Actions (`actions.ts`) with the page that uses them
- No default exports from component files — named exports only (exception: page.tsx and layout.tsx which Next.js requires as default exports)

### Styling
Use CSS variables from globals.css. Never hardcode colours.

| Token | Value | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `var(--brand-accent)` | Set per brand | Primary actions, active states |
| `var(--color-bg)` | #0a0a0f | Page background |
| `var(--color-surface-1)` | #111118 | Cards, sidebar |
| `var(--color-surface-2)` | #1a1a24 | Inputs, secondary cards |
| `var(--color-surface-3)` | #24242f | Hover states, badges |
| `var(--color-border)` | rgba(255,255,255,0.08) | All borders |
| `var(--color-text-primary)` | rgba(255,255,255,0.92) | Headings, labels |
| `var(--color-text-secondary)` | rgba(255,255,255,0.5) | Body, descriptions |
| `var(--color-text-tertiary)` | rgba(255,255,255,0.28) | Hints, placeholders |

- Use Tailwind for layout and spacing
- Use inline styles when referencing CSS variables (Tailwind cannot interpolate them)
- Border radius scale: 6px (small), 8px (default), 10–12px (cards), 16px (large panels)

### AI providers (M3+)
NEVER import `openai`, `@anthropic-ai/sdk`, or any AI SDK outside of `src/lib/ai/provider.ts`.
This is the single abstraction point. Everything else calls `provider.ts`.

